reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice 2 TB Gen 4 SSD.
reviews.reviewText: This purchase was part of an overall upgrade to my Gigabyte Z590 Aorus Elite AX motherboard to include a i7 11700K CPU and 64GB G.Skill DDR4 3200. I'm not going to bore you with charts or graphs with benchmark photos that I'm sure are already plentiful. I will state that going from a Gen 3 SSD to fully supported Gen 4 NVMe M.2 drive is physically noticeable. OS Boot to login and desktop is quicker, app load times quicker, no noticeable heat throttling with the heat spreader and heat sink cover. For the price this little jewel comes at, I have no problem recommending it to any gaming enthusiast, hobbyist, photo or video editor, pretty much anyone on a shoestring budget looking for a cost effective solution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent cost for performance.
reviews.reviewText: I do tech support work as a side job and ended up buying two of these drives one for my client's Dell laptop and the other as an external storage system for my XBOX Series X.I was able to clone my client's old 500GB HDD that was failing and ended up boosting the boot time from 11 mins to less than 15 seconds.Due to the fact that the laptop was manufactured in 2010 and had been upgraded from Windows 8 to 10 it was having some hardware issues specifically the HDD and Ram.As these two were failing they were causing Windows to regularly blue screen.My client was afraid that he was going to loose all of his data so I did an emergency backup to a flash drive just in case the HDD failed before the replacement arrived.Fortunately the old drive held out long enough and I was able to get the laptop back up and running.The other drive is attached to my Series X for use with my XBOX One games and the difference between it and my old 4TB HDD game drive is phenomenal.I highlg recomend this brand, the cost per Gigabyte and performance is justification enough.
